PLANETARY TEXTURES

The equirectangular surface texture for Earth in
`brutalist-void-portfolio-template/public/textures/earth.jpg` is derived
from the NASA Blue Marble image collection (Visible Earth, image record
57752, "Land — Shallow Topography"). NASA imagery is in the public
domain and may be used without permission or fee.

The Pluto surface texture `public/textures/pluto.webp` is derived from
the NASA / Johns Hopkins APL / Southwest Research Institute global
color mosaic produced from New Horizons LORRI + MVIC imagery
(2015 flyby). Source: science.nasa.gov/resource/pluto-global-color-map/.
NASA imagery is in the public domain.

The equirectangular surface textures for the Sun, Mercury, Venus, Mars,
Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune (all under `public/textures/`)
are © Solar System Scope (https://www.solarsystemscope.com/textures),
licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International
license (CC BY 4.0). Attribution is given here and is required of any
downstream re-use of those specific files.

